===================INSTALL HTTPD & PHP in  all app the server===================

    sudo yum install httpd php php-mysqlnd php-pdo php-gd php-mbstring -y
	sudo systemctl enable httpd
    sudo systemctl start httpd
	
	Change the HTTPD listen port if needed ( HTTPD.conf file)
	
Note: Make sure you add the right users and credentials in /var/www/html/index.php file


===================ON Database server --- Setup MARIA DB===================

    sudo yum install mariadb-server -y
    sudo systemctl enable mariadb
    sudo systemctl start mariadb
	
	
===================CREATE DB user for APP access to Database===================

	mysql -u root -p
    CREATE DATABASE DB_name;
    CREATE USER 'user'@'%' IDENTIFIED BY 'your_secure_password';   ( Make sure you create user for remote hosts )
    GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DB_name* TO 'user'@'%';
    FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
    EXIT;

Single Command  --->>>  GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON my_database.* TO 'my_user'@'%' IDENTIFIED BY 'my_passwd';

Now restart Maria DB - then app should be able to connect with Database.

===============Task DONE ===============================================


L	Linux	The operating system — the foundation that runs everything else.
A	Apache	The web server — handles HTTP requests from users (browsers) and serves web pages.
M	MySQL / MariaDB	The database — stores data like user info, blog posts, products, etc.
P	PHP	Server-side scripting language — generates dynamic content (like login pages, dashboards).


User opens a website in a browser:

http://example.com


-- Apache receives the request.

-- If the page is static (.html), Apache serves it directly.
-- If the page is dynamic (.php), Apache sends it to PHP.

--PHP executes the code:

--Reads/writes data in MySQL/MariaDB.

--Generates HTML content.

--Apache sends the HTML back to the browser.

--The user sees the webpage.
